# Bundle maintainer (local)

Read gitignored **`MAINTAINER.md`** and **`AGENTS-LOCAL.md`** when present (installed by `./snippets/bootstrap-maintainer-local.sh`).

## Canonical paths (this repo)

| Artifact | Path |
|----------|------|
| Core workflows | [docs/workflows/](docs/workflows/) |
| LSI overlay (authoring) | [overlays/lsi/](overlays/lsi/) |
| Router | [which-workflow.md](which-workflow.md) |
| OpenSpec | `openspec/changes/<slug>/` (tracked) |
| Slash commands | `.cursor/commands/` (gitignored, local install) |

**Do not** edit or create `.lsi/workflows/` in this repo. **Do not** run `adopt.py --target .`.

## OpenSpec lifecycle

Follow [overlays/lsi/docs/workflows/openspec-git-integration.md](overlays/lsi/docs/workflows/openspec-git-integration.md).

- Changes: **`openspec/changes/<slug>/`**
- Config: [openspec/config.yaml](../../openspec/config.yaml)
- Production close on **`main`** when using `/lsi:close` (bundle has no `staging` branch)

Branch policy: [.cursor/rules/local-branch-workflow.mdc](local-branch-workflow.mdc) if installed.

## Workflow routing

1. [which-workflow.md](which-workflow.md)
2. Matching spec under `docs/workflows/` or `overlays/lsi/docs/workflows/`
3. [examples/](examples/) for good vs weak output

## Commits and PRs

Tracked [.cursor/rules/commit-pr-conventions.mdc](commit-pr-conventions.mdc) applies. Only `git commit` when the user explicitly asks.

## Adopter sync

When user asks to re-sync adopters, read `MAINTAINER.md` adopt loop and run `verify-all-adopters.sh` after adopt.
